## 10. Lifecycle status

Our existing stoplight vocabulary, pulled into this framework by
reference so designers find the full naming picture in one place.

| Status | What it means |
|---|---|
| **Placeholder** | Exists in name only. No design or code yet. |
| **Blocked** | Work has started but is waiting on something. |
| **In Progress** | Actively being designed or built. |
| **Review** | Design is settled, in review with stakeholders. |
| **Production** | Shipped and supported. |
| **Deprecated** | Being retired. Do not use for new work. |

These are reflected on the Figma page-name stoplights (🟠 🟡 🟢 ⚫)
and on the status badge on every component page in the docs site.
Source of truth for the current status of any component is its
`status.json` file under `uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/`. See
[`uds-component-checklist.mdc`](./uds-component-checklist.mdc) for
the per-component file contract.

