## How this rule is used

The skills that build or update components should pick names from
the framework rather than guessing from siblings or inventing new
words:

- [`generate-uds-figma-component`](../skills/generate-uds-figma-component/SKILL.md)
 — the factory's "agreed vocabulary" *is* this framework. Phase A's
 state matrix and variant axes draw from sections 1, 4, and 6.
 Phase B's variant property names and values follow section 7's
 casing rule.
- [`new-component`](../skills/new-component/SKILL.md) — when
 scaffolding a fresh `spec.json`, populate `states[]` with the
 names from section 1, not free-form text.
- [`sync-figma-component-spec`](../skills/sync-figma-component-spec/SKILL.md)
 — when migrating an existing component's spec to match a fresh
 Figma read, prefer the framework's names over preserving legacy
 inconsistent names. Renames are classified per
 [`uds-figma-change-classification.mdc`](./uds-figma-change-classification.mdc).
- [`spec-audit`](../agents/spec-audit.md) — completeness scoring
 stays the same, but a future enhancement can flag specs whose
 state / variant / property names don't match the framework.

## How this rule relates to others

| Rule | Relationship |
|---|---|
| [`uds-design-language.mdc`](./uds-design-language.mdc) | The visual partner. Design Language tells you *how* Pressed looks; this rule tells you it's called *Pressed*, not *Active*. Section 11 of Design Language is the original Pressed/Checked/Selected/Current distinction — this rule extends it from the visual layer to the spec-naming layer. |
| [`uds-content-schema.mdc`](./uds-content-schema.mdc) | The schema contract. Lists the fields (`states[]`, `props[]`, `events[]`, etc.) — this rule provides the canonical values for those fields. |
| [`uds-component-checklist.mdc`](./uds-component-checklist.mdc) | The completeness contract. Lists what files a component needs — this rule provides the vocabulary the spec inside them should use. |
| [`uds-figma-factory-quality.mdc`](./uds-figma-factory-quality.mdc) | The factory-build quality gates. Process is there; vocabulary is here. |

## Out of scope

- **Backfilling existing component specs** to match the framework.
 Each component picks up the new names the next time it gets touched
 by a Figma → docs sync. This rule establishes the framework; the
 sync skills migrate names component-by-component on schedule.
- **Renaming existing CSS classes or data attributes** under
 `uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/<id>.css`. Code under that path
 follows Figma per [`uds-source-of-truth.mdc`](./uds-source-of-truth.mdc),
 so any rename routes through a designer-led round trip.
- **Hard-enforcing the vocabulary in `spec.schema.json`**. Possible
 follow-up once existing specs have caught up.
